Preamble

This license governs the rights to the FantasyMapForge software (the
"Software") and the outputs created by using the Software ("Generated
Content"). The intent is to:
- Allow anyone to use and modify the Software for their own purposes;
- Allow users to keep and commercially exploit any Generated Content they
   create; and
- Prohibit commercial distribution of the Software itself without a
   separate commercial license from the copyright holder.

Definitions

- "Software": the FantasyMapForge application and all source, binaries,
   documentation, assets, and associated files included in this repository.
- "Generated Content": any images, maps, models, or other outputs produced
   by running or using the Software, whether processed or unprocessed.
- "Commercial Distribution": selling, licensing, sublicensing, or otherwise
   providing the Software (source or binary) to third parties for a fee or as
   part of a paid product, service, or distribution bundle.
- "Service": an online or hosted offering (SaaS) that runs the Software to
   produce Generated Content for users.

Grant of Rights

1. Use and Modification

    You may use, run, study, copy, and modify the Software for any purpose,
    including for internal commercial purposes. This includes using the
    Software to create Generated Content for a business, research, or
    creative project.

2. Generated Content

    You retain all rights, title, and interest in and to any Generated
    Content you produce with the Software. You may use, modify, publish,
    distribute, and sell your Generated Content for any purpose, including
    commercial purposes, without attribution or additional permission.

Restrictions

3. Commercial Distribution of the Software

    You may NOT commercially distribute, sell, sublicense, or otherwise make
    available the Software itself or modified versions of the Software to
    third parties for a fee, except under a separate, explicit commercial
    license granted by the copyright holder. Examples of prohibited acts
    without a commercial license include:

    - Selling compiled binaries or packaged versions of the Software.
    - Including the Software in a paid SDK, library, or product bundle that
       consumers must pay to receive.
    - Re-licensing the Software under a proprietary/commercial license and
       distributing it for a fee.

4. Free Redistribution

    You may redistribute the Software (source or binaries) for free, provided
    that you retain this license and copyright notice and do not impose
    additional restrictions that conflict with this license.

5. Services (SaaS)

    Running the Software to provide Generated Content to users as a hosted
    service (SaaS) is allowed. However, the act of packaging the Software and
    distributing it to third parties for use (see "Commercial Distribution")
    is restricted without a commercial license. If you plan to redistribute a
    copy of the Software itself as part of a paid service offering, please
    contact the copyright holder for a commercial license.

Attribution

6. Attribution

    If you redistribute the Software (including modified versions), you must
    include this license file and copyright notice. No additional attribution
    is required to publish or sell Generated Content.

Commercial Licensing Offer

7. Commercial License Option

    Copyright holders may offer a commercial license for entities who wish to
    distribute or sell the Software itself or to include it within paid
    products. Contact the copyright holder to negotiate terms for commercial
    redistribution.

Warranty and Liability

8. Disclaimer of Warranty

    THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
    IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,
